2007-10-25  mefyl  <mefyl@lrde.epita.fr>

	Use boost to handle paths.
	* include/kernel/userver.hh,
	* src/userver.cc:
	(UServer::find_file): Use boost::filesystem::path to open files,
	to avoid portability problem such as the directory separator.

2007-10-24  Matthieu Nottale  <nottale@gostai.com>

	Correct uobject behavior.
	When a c++ code reads an UVar, it must triggers notifyaccess, except
	if this read occurrs in a notifychange callback: in this case the
	value is allready up2date, and it would create a potential infinite
	loop to call the notifyaccess.
	* include/kernel/uvariable.hh: Add inSetTarget and isInSetTarget
	  accessor.
	* src/uvar.cc:
	   - invoque uvariable->get() in in() except if inSetTarget()
	   - Add missing call to remote callbacks in setTarget()
	   - call selfSet, setTarget but not setSensorVal in operator = for
	     !owned !variable->autoUpdate case
	* src/uvariable.cc: set/clear inSetTarget in setTarget and setSensor.

2007-10-24  Matthieu Nottale  <nottale@gostai.com>

	Fix notifychange when called from a C++ variable update.
	* src/uvar.cc: Call methods in the correct order, otherwise
	  callbacks are called with the old value.

2007-10-24  Matthieu Nottale  <nottale@gostai.com>

	Fix display of value returned by a bound uobject method.
	* src/ucommand.cc: Replace old display code that does not work
	 anymore by new code (copy-pasted from below in the same function).

